Feature Introduction, the best Chinese character report

This is people's "meet the good" section, where members of the editorial staff share some of the best experiences they have had in their own lives -- in Florida, we share stories together, and we share life with you in the future. What would you like to see more of after the outbreak?
It seems that in one night, the street of primroses are in full bloom. Anyone passing by couldn't help taking out their mobile phone and taking a few photos. Nature's stable inertia gives people a solid sense of security, no matter what human society, as long as the time, the flowers will open.
As things gradually get back on track, some expectations start to kick in, such as planning a trip next year or wherever. The unfamiliar streets, the queues at the attractions, the smell of wet earth in the forest, the glare of the sun on the waves... all sound distant and familiar. It may not all work out in the end, but it's good to have something to look forward to.

RECOMMENDED DESTINATIONS: Kunming, Guiyang

Recommended by an Xiaoqing

After the outbreak is over, destinations that are too far away are unlikely to be reached in the short term. If I had a three-day break, I would most like to go to Guiyang and Kunming.

If you go to Guiyang, you want to walk the streets and eat whatever you can find. Chihuahua, Fried Potato, sausage noodles, baked potato, beef noodles. At night, we'd eat the barbed wire barbeque in the plastic shack. But my top recommendation is the Kang Pot area in one of the city markets. The district has dozens of stalls with young Niang sisters in Guiyang, dressed in white coats and sanitary hats, with the air of someone who has just been re-employed as a third-line factory worker in a Wang Xiaoshuai film.

The best food inside is stinky Tofu, mashed potatoes, pig intestines, beef, Leek, lotus flower white, with dried sea pepper noodles and the light of Guiyang as Myrica Rubra, entering a stage of life not controlled by Internet celebrities and Kol for a while.

In addition, the night can not be missed is the small stick barbecue. Guiyang has a street (Gai) is dedicated to whole barbecue, it is responsible to say that the small stick barbecue is the country's second-best incense. Number one on my side is the signature barbecue in old Xichang. Aside from the fresh little kebabs of beef, streaky pork, chicken skin and cockles, brain lovers shouldn't miss out on the must-have points. This side of the brain is a tin foil or Lotus White base, the brain skin covered with folded ear root, sesame, scallion, pepper, sea pepper, the smell of no trace, only protein and vanilla embedded each other's aroma.

After a barbecue, take a walk around the high and low Guiyang city, hit a balloon stand if you're lucky, 10 bucks for 20 rounds of ammunition, and the moment you pick up an air gun, you feel like you're playing a hustler. If you're lucky, you'll find a wild karaoke bar by the river or under the bridge. You can't buy a song for two dollars.

It's a real playground for the wanderer and the Foodie.

Those who can't make it can follow@dare to, the Yunnan local food blogger on Weibo, a powerful character who visits the market almost every day. His pictures are often a great way for me to get out of bed and live my life.

Recommended Destination: Berlin

Recommended by: May

I like to plan my trip well in advance, and I like to buy my ticket long in advance, confident that if I buy my ticket well in advance, I'll be able to get out of the House against all odds. But it turned out to be a bust for the last two flights, including to Berlin this year.

I bought a round-trip ticket from Beijing to Berlin for the May Day holiday last November, which adds up to eight days of vacation plus annual leave. But the outbreak, coupled with the uncertain state of the European epidemic, a few days ago has returned the tickets.

The reason for wanting to go to Berlin is simple: to see the forest, to drink beer, to meet friends. I once met several German girls on a hike in Russia. They were very similar. They had long summer holidays. They went out alone, without suitcases, with a 30L bag on their back, dressed simply, simple and strong, and walked around quietly. They talked about the mountains, the parks and the trees, the chaos and the youth of Berlin.

I bought a lot of books for the trip. There is the diary of Berlin, written by a journalist, and Berlin: A portrait of a city, about the city of Berlin, which contains many detailed street maps. I have even read the incoherent collection of Berlin. But because of the outbreak, none of that knowledge will come in handy for a while. But Berlin is still my first choice for travel, and if things get better in the fall, I'll go again. You don't see Berlin in the spring, you see Berlin in the fall.

To write this recommendation, I dug up correspondence with my German friend Bettina. After we met in Russia, we hiked together again in Beijing, and she continued her journey, describing what she had seen in a letter. The English passage is so concise and beautiful that I have read it many times. Now that we're all stuck at home and can't get out of the House for a while, let's share this fascinating journey.

After leaving Beijing, I went to Almaty, where I stayed for a while -- Lake Almaty in autumn has amazing colors. When it started snowing in Almaty, I took a bus to Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan, and the snow followed, pushing me to the Andalucía, Colombia in southern Spain. It was still a warm October, the beaches were endless and the seas were rough. I met my parents in Grenada and flew from Madrid to Colombia for the final leg of my journey. When I returned to Germany, it was Christmas, and I was warmly welcomed by my family and friends, who made me cookies. "

Recommended Destination: Tangjiahe Nature Reserve

Recommended by: Tu Yuqing

Last fall, I went to the tangjiahe nature reserve in Sichuan Province for what was probably the happiest interview of my life. It was the first time I had seen so many red leaves stacked on top of each other, such as the Brown Beech leaves, the Bear's paw-like leaves of a wood tree, and the names of the mosses, interesting to know, Trametes versicolor -- they grow horizontally on a deadwood branch, and if you tilt the branch in the process, Trametes versicolor stops growing and finds another one.

Occasionally, you can see the Dung of the antelope passing by. It looks like a small black ball, and it doesn't smell, but the Dung of the Tibetan Macaque always appears in the middle of the road. Don't step on it. I was lucky enough to catch sight of a MUNTJAC grazing on the slope, and as soon as he heard the sound of human footsteps, he put up his white tail as a reminder to his companion -- Foshan -- that someone was coming, and we ran. The farther up the hill the fog thickened, like rain that had not yet fallen. The station Master said that in autumn and winter, when there is no fog, you can see the snow line on the mountain.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yoon suk-won

The forest has a particularly wonderful attraction, and everyone who lives in it seems to be getting smaller. There's a girl in the reserve, she wants to keep the smell of the forest, she gets a distilling machine, she makes her own oils. When I heard this story, I remembered the game when I was a child and my friends pounded leaves to make perfume. The magazine photographer I came with, picked up a few ACORNS that had been eaten by monkeys and squirrels, and said, "we're all squirrels. ".

I and stationmaster agree, when spring comes, want to sign up to do volunteer inside the mountain. The engagement was delayed because of the epidemic. Now when I think of the forest, I can smell the smell of wet earth. I've been sitting at home for so long, I miss that smell.

RECOMMENDED DESTINATION: Netherlands

Recommended by: August

When it's over, I'm dying to go back to the Netherlands. I always felt the people there were more relaxed and sunny. Of course, this may have something to do with the fact that most Dutch people speak good English, and only when people communicate with each other do they feel something. Walking along the canals of Amsterdam, walking through the streets of Florida is an experience I would have had in any city in Europe, but in my memory Parisians are exquisite, Barcelona is lazy, and only Ames, it's total freedom. That kind of freedom made me miss being locked up for more than ten days.

There are plenty of other memorable images: Dutch men and women, mostly tall, pedaling their bikes furiously without umbrellas even in rainy weather, and street dwellers with picture windows on the ground floor who never pull the curtains, looking inside, any room has a design that could be published in a home magazine; standing in the Van Gogh Museum, it's easy to get a deep stare into his paintings and lose track of time; In the aquatic product market, my friend took me to eat a kind of fish which could be eaten raw, and the fishy smell didn't seem to go away..

Recommended Destination: Xinjiang

Recommended by Bogwood

Originally had been planning to go to Iceland this year, where the weather is freezing, I think when I go must put a bottle Erguotou. After a cup to the sun, a cup to the Aurora, what troubles are in the wine to drink, think all feel delicious.

This outbreak has shattered all dreams, and it is foreseeable that for a long time, travel abroad will be more or less divided, and the resulting guard and discomfort will not know how long it will take to subside, but either way, it's just a matter of time.

So if you ask me the most recommended place to go after the epidemic ended, my own answer is Xinjiang.

In 2017, I went to Xinjiang to drive myself with friends. Along the way, chasing the mountains and rivers running, large grassland, early morning forest, snow-covered Kanas, blazing Sunshine and Water under the Reeds, I do not know where the sudden emergence of a large sunflower, in front of nature, all men are equal, man is equal to the birds of the air, and to the horses of the Earth, and to all things in the world, and it is only in the widest places that one can understand why the animals in the zoo are unhappy, because they are not free.

Because all the way west, the BGM on the car is related to journey to the West, the most repeated is the 86 version of the original sound of daughter's love, which recorded a part of Zhu Bajie's voice, Xuanzang and daughter of the king farewell, when the song began, "the king is rich and powerful, so are the rules and regulations. " Zhu Bajie looked at the tearful king and hummed, "the daughter King is very sentimental! "

The other is a second-hand rose version of "why the West is far away" , in which Diplodocus's voice turns the song into a sour song, "Why should the West be far away, joy is here, joy is here tonight, joy is here tonight, " the chorus at the end of each chorus

Also in Xinjiang, one night when I was on the road, I saw the biggest, brightest, most beautiful moon of my life. I looked at the moon. The noisy car was quiet for a long time. A little friend thought of something sad, and I cried my eyes out. The beauty of Xinjiang has its own kind of vastness, which can absorb and accommodate a lot of things, people's troubles, the passage of time, all of us entangled.

I think most of us have spent the longest period of our lives living in a house. When all is over, we will go to the vast expanse of Xinjiang and take a look around. We will shout and sing, that's probably a good exit.

RECOMMENDED DESTINATION: Wuhan

Recommended by: Do

I am now in Wuhan, because work to ride the Yangtze River twice a day, quickly familiar with Wuhan's main streets and landmarks. In Wuhan after the closure of the city, the Iron Gates of the residential area were locked, people outside could not get in, and people inside could not get out; supermarkets and convenience stores only accept community purchases, so there were no individual tourists; on the Yangsigang Yangtze River Bridge, a car would pass in seven or eight minutes, two-way, six-lane streets are empty enough for a football match; not to mention the usual cacophony of Hubu Alley, Jiqing street and Yellow Crane Tower, the city's calling card, where time stands still.

A friend asked me if my days were numbered, but they weren't. But there was no one on the street, just a few food delivery guys and me passing by; there were always a few red armbands in Hazmat suits at the community entrance, standing outside the Iron Gates with their thermoguns. Looking at the same scene every day the same people, the same locked shops and anti-epidemic slogans, the loss of change, silence of the city let me lose the sense of time.

Twenty days ago, I took a picture of a homeless man sitting under a tree full of flowers. Yesterday, when I went back, it was a dead branch. The first wave of spring flowers had already fallen. It's been a while, hasn't it. I live downstairs, the second wave of flowers are also open, there are Magnolia, there is a kind of spring to know the flowers, called Purple Leaf Cherry Plum.

If you ask me where I would like to travel after the epidemic, I think it is still Wuhan, because I would like to see her normal, full of smoke and fire. I want to go to the bar of Pub No. 18 and listen to people talk about alcohol and freedom. I want to be with my friends in Wuhan on a hot summer day, jump naked into the East L. , and let the joy and the spirit spread across the lake. People are no longer locked in their homes. I want to see them fighting and kissing on the street. I want to hear them honking and speeding as they drive across the Yangtze River Bridge.

Of course, I especially want to see those who recover, I want to see them walking in the streets of Wuhan, through the summer flowering, through the autumn flowering, I want to see what time looks like, such a hot city, I want to see life still go on, and never stop.

May, Wuhan
